10/05/2004
PORTOROZ, Slovenia -- Parliamentary representatives of the Adriatic-Ionian Initiative (AII) member countries meet Monday (10 May) in the Slovenian town of Portoroz. The AII was established in 2000 and co-ordinates the efforts of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH), Greece, Croatia, Italy, Serbia-Montenegro and Slovenia to ensure stability and prosperity in the region.
In other news, right- and centre-wing political parties from countries across the region met in Banja Luka, BiH, over the weekend. Participants from BiH, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Serbia-Montenegro, as well as Britain and Sweden attended the meeting. (OHR Sources - 10/05/04; HINA, STA, Pincom.info, Fena - 09/05/04)
